  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project works in the upper Amazon River Basin, specifically in the Valleys of the Apur&#xED;mac, Ene and Mantaro Rivers (VRAEM), to promote cocoa as an alternative to coca production. The goals is to help producers achieve an increase in their income from cocoa sales, through three objectives: 1. Cocoa producers and producers increase their production and productivity at the farm level. 2. Cocoa producers and producers improve the quality of dry cocoa beans according to market requirements. 3. Cocoa producers are organized business and articulated to the market in an organized and planned manner.</narrative>
  </description>
